The paper proposes a deep learning architecture for interior tomography reconstruction, which involves image processing and computer vision techniques, suggesting that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning also suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the computational complexity of existing methods, suggesting that it may belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
